⠀

"I'm so sad I didn't try this salad sooner. This is definitely going into my rotation."⠀
⠀
Oh my gosh, please do not spend any more of your days NOT having had this delicious salad like reader Jessica! It is a life not lived. It has everything -- sweet, savory, crunch, bits of juicy mango, and a spicy peanut dressing you will dream about. It's all the things you need, live your best life.⠀
⠀
Quinoa Salad: ⠀
2-3 cups shelled edamame⠀
2 cups quinoa⠀
1 cucumber, diced⠀
1-2 bell peppers, diced⠀
2 ripe mangoes, diced⠀
3 carrots, shredded⠀
half a head of purple cabbage, shredded⠀
sliced almonds, peanuts, or cashews for topping⠀
⠀
Peanut Dressing: ⠀
1/2 cup creamy peanut butter⠀
1/3 cup soy sauce⠀
1/3 cup white vinegar⠀
1/4 cup sesame oil⠀
1-2 tablespoons chili paste⠀
2 tablespoons honey⠀
1 clove garlic⠀
1 knob of fresh ginger, peeled⠀
⠀
Instructions: ⠀
1. Cook up the quinoa and edamame according to package directions. ⠀
2. Chop up all your produce. ⠀
3. Blitz up your dressing in a food processor or blender. ⠀
4. Toss everything together and enjoy!⠀
⠀

node.text:
Is there any cuter couple than pan-fried juicy shrimp and silky chewy fettuccine? Absolutely not, #couplegoals. And when those two are dressed all matchy matchy in spicy-but-not-hot, garlicky, creamy, kinda lemony, red pepper butter sauce? So cuuuuute. (And also super quick and delicious and other more food-appropriate descriptors.)⠀
⠀
Red Pepper Garlic Butter:
1 cup softened unsalted butter 
3 cloves garlic
Juice and zest of 1 lemon
3/4 cup fresh herbs (like parsley, green onion, and cilantro) 
8 ounces jarred roasted red peppers 
1 teaspoon salt 

Shrimp and Fettuccine:
16 ounces raw shrimp 
8 ounces uncooked fettuccine 
1/2 cup heavy whipping cream 
3/4 cup reserved pasta water 
Greens, lemons, and salt for serving 

Instructions: 
1. Pulse all the ingredients for the butter in the food processor until smooth and set aside. 
2. Cook noodles according to package directions. Add pasta back to warm pot and toss with 2-3 tablespoons of red pepper garlic butter, cream, and pasta water. Add more pasta water to thin out the sauce as needed. 
3. Cook up shrimp in 2 tablespoons of red pepper garlic butter. 
4. Divide the pasta and shrimp among 3-4 plates and enjoy! 
⠀
